    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-10T08:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-10T08:44:00-05:00" n="542"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.515/61: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-10T13:00:00-00:44"
                            >March 10, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>66. From McBride. Legation’s 62, March 8, 10 a.m. President Barclay is willing to
                    proceed with monetary reform immediately provided some general arrangement such
                    as suggested in No. 62 is found practicable by American officials.
                    [McBride.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
